User critique (verbatim):
  'DEFENCE / MISSILES showing POWERGRID NTPC BHEL ABB SIEMENS is wrong.
   These are not the highest-beta beneficiaries of India's defense
   manufacturing cycle.'
  'Map BOTTLENECK -> SCARCE ENABLER, not THEME -> LARGE CAP.'
  'Stop weighting PSU megacaps and obvious index proxies.'

THIS PATCH:

1. EXPANDED INDIA_ROSTER L1 — defence/aerospace specialists (no hardcoded
   tier mapping; just makes them DISCOVERABLE in the seed):
     PARASDEF.NS    Paras Defence — defence optics + EW + naval systems
     MTARTECH.NS    MTAR — precision components for nuclear/ISRO/defence
     DATAPATTNS.NS  Data Patterns — radar / EW / avionics electronics
     ASTRAMICRO.NS  Astra Microwave — RF seekers / radar subsystems
     ZENTEC.NS      Zen Technologies — combat training simulators
     IDEAFORGE.NS   IdeaForge — military drones (UAV indigenisation)
     APOLLO.NS      Apollo Micro — naval/aerospace mission systems
     CYIENTDLM.NS   Cyient DLM — EMS for aerospace + defence + medical
     UNIMECH.NS     Unimech Aerospace — precision machining
     BHARATFORG.NS  Bharat Forge defence vertical (ATAGS / Kalyani M4)
     SOLARINDS.NS   Solar Industries — explosives + defence munitions

   And power-equipment specialists:
     SHILCHTECH.NS  Shilchar Technologies — distribution / furnace transformers
     VOLTAMP.NS     Voltamp — power transformers (lead-time pricing power)
     TRIL.NS        Transformers & Rectifiers India — EHV transformers
     SKIPPER.NS     Skipper — transmission towers + polymer pipes
     GENUSPOWER.NS  Genus Power — smart meters (AMI rollout)
     KPIGREEN.NS    KPI Green — solar EPC + IPP

2. DROPPED L5 from DEFENSE / AEROSPACE / NUCLEAR NODE_RULES_IN
   The L5 platform layer was pulling TCS / INFY / WIPRO / RELIANCE under
   defence + nuclear cards — pure theme dilution.  Per user critique:
   'Generic IT services inside every theme is diluting the engine.'

3. RE-WIRED MANDATORY INJECTS:
   DEFENSE_INFRA -> Data Patterns / Paras / Astra Micro / MTAR / Apollo /
                    Zen Tech / ideaForge / Cyient DLM / Unimech / Bharat
                    Forge / Solar Industries
                    (NOT POWERGRID / NTPC / SIEMENS / ABB which are
                    grid names that don't capture defence orderbook torque)
   AEROSPACE_INFRA -> MTAR / Paras / Data Patterns / Unimech / Cyient DLM
   NUCLEAR_INFRA -> MTAR (precision components for NPCIL fuel handling) +
                    BHEL + Paras + Apollo + Bharat Forge + NTPC; drop L5
   RENEWABLE_INFRA -> KPI Green / Voltamp / Shilchar / TRIL / Skipper /
                      Genus / Adani Green ahead of POWERGRID / NTPC megacaps
   ENERGY_INFRA -> Shilchar / Voltamp / TRIL / Skipper / Genus / CG Power /
                   KEC / ABB / Siemens / POWERGRID / NTPC / BHEL — order
                   matters, megacaps still present but lower convexity

4. NEW: convexity_score field on every LayerTicker
   Pattern-based (NOT a hardcoded ticker→tier dictionary):
     +30 if SMALL_CAP, +18 if MID_CAP                  (size convexity)
     +20 if STRONG leverage, +10 if MEDIUM             (pricing power)
     +10 if mandatory                                   (structural fit)
     + 5 if discovered (news-evidence)
     -25 if ticker matches generic-megacap regex
         (POWERGRID/NTPC/RELIANCE/TCS/INFY/WIPRO/HCLTECH/ONGC/COALINDIA/
          SBIN/HDFC/HDFCBANK/ICICIBANK/KOTAKBANK/AXISBANK/HINDUNILVR/ITC/LT)
     - 5 if accumulator_score > 100 (institutional saturation proxy)
   Score capped 0-100.

5. RE-SORT WITHIN LAYER:
   Tier A first (existing logic), THEN by convexity_score desc instead of
   by leverage rank.  Net effect: small/midcap precision (Data Patterns,
   MTAR, Shilchar, Voltamp) rises ABOVE generic megacaps within the same
   layer.  Per user: 'orderbook torque + operating leverage + rerating
   potential — not theme awareness'.

Type-check clean.
